&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Registered General Nurse (Band 5)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;King’s Staff Bank are recruiting Registered General Nurses to join the Princess Royal University Hospital&#39;s (PRUH) bank of flexible workers. Work shifts that suit you, with fuss-free online timesheets and weekly pay!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have both ad-hoc shifts and &lt;strong&gt;regular shift patterns available. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Bank nurses are invaluable to us and in return for your dedication and commitment, we offer the following benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities to work across all King&#39;s sites, gaining invaluable knowledge and experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Priority of shifts over agency workers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Onsite office and designated bank reps to offer fast support daily&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-book shifts wherever you are&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fuss-free Electronic Timesheets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Weekly pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An onsite recruitment, compliance and bookings team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to free Bank Partners Core Skills Training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•NMC Registration&lt;br /&gt;•A minimum of 6 months experience working within the NHS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The PRUH is a friendly, local hospital in Farnborough Common where you can truly feel a part of the NHS family, whilst also working at one of London&#39;s largest and best-known NHS trusts as a valued member of the team. We have an on-site team that can get you working as soon as possible and a dedicated bookings team to make sure that you can work where you want, when you want.&lt;/p&gt;
